subject: Re: [junit] Implicit super constructor TestCase() is not visible for default constructor. Mu
msgSnippet: ... That is strange. Are you /certain/ you are using JUnit 3.8.1 and not some earlier version? -- J. B. (Joe) Rainsberger :: http://www.jbrains.info Your guide
messageBody:
slopescratcher wrote:
> Hi,
>
> after Eclipse createt an jUnit test case for me, I get following error
> message shown at the class name:
>
> Implicit super constructor TestCase() is not visible for default
> constructor. Must define an explicit constructor
>
> The code is not edited up to now:
>
> package at.tugraz.genome.maspectras.utils.action;
>
> import junit.framework.TestCase;
>
> public class ReturnPathUtilTest extends TestCase {
>
> /*
> * Test method for
> 'at.tugraz.genome.maspectras.utils.action.ReturnPathUtil.parseForReturnPath(String)'
> */
> public void testParseForReturnPath() {
> // TODO Auto-generated method stub
>
> }
>
> }

That is strange. Are you /certain/ you are using JUnit 3.8.1 and not
some earlier version?
